CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Presenting Scholarship - It isn't all socializing for members of the Pittsburgh Chapter of Squaws. They also sponsor an annual scholarship project.  The group awarded over $1,100 in scholarships this year.  During their last holiday fete, Mrs. William Stewart, scholarship chairman presented checks to Miss Cathy McCall, Leo Wood Jr., Cynthia Jones and Alfred Little (See "Things to Talk About" for details)."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. William Stewart, presenting scholarship checks to Cathy McCall, Leo Wood Jr., Cynthia Jones, and Alfred Little, during Squaws "Cotton Extravaganza" Dinner-Dance in Holiday House, Monroeville
